iisa fortress on Svartholm Island. In the summer there is a ferry from Laivasilta a few hundred meters south of the town center, ferry tickets cost €15 for a roundtrip."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Loviisa church"],["alt="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat=60.4562"],["long=26.2229"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=The road to Loviisa from the west seems to lead right into the red tile church that is a one of the most visible landmarks of the town."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Lovisa nuclear power plant"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.fortum.com\/en\/energy-production\/nuclear-power\/loviisa-1--2\/pages\/default.aspx"],["email="],["address="],["lat=60.3707"],["long=26.3447"],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Finland's oldest nuclear power plant is located on Hästholmen island, 15km southeast of the town center. Visits need to be pre-arranged but you can always look at the plant from a distance."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Strömfors ironworks"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.stromforsinruukki.fi"],["email="],["address=Ruukintie 11A"],["lat=60.5238"],["long=26.4722"],["directions=in Ruotsinpyhtää village, east of Loviisa"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=The old ironworks of Strömfors (Swedish)\/ Ruotsinpyhtää (Finnish) is today a museum."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Hotel Degerby"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.degerby.com\/fi\/hotel-degerby"],["email=reception@degerby.com"],["address=Brandensteininkatu 17"],["lat=60.4572"],["long=26.2283"],["directions="],["phone=+358 19 50561"],[